<h1>
    Reactive Form in Angular - Introduction to FormBuilder
</h1>

<hr>

ðŸ”µ What is FormBuilder?

1.FormBuilder is an Angular service.

2.It is used in Reactive Forms.

3.It provides a shortcut way to create FormGroup, FormControl, and FormArray.

4.It reduces repetitive code.

5.It makes form code cleaner and more readable.


ðŸ”µ Why Use FormBuilder?

1.Reduces boilerplate code.

2.Improves readability.

3.Makes large forms easier to manage.

4.Preferred in real-world applications.


ðŸ”µ Syntax Difference

1.Without FormBuilder

userForm = new FormGroup({
name: new FormControl(''),
email: new FormControl('')
});

2.With FormBuilder

constructor(private fb: FormBuilder) {}

userForm = this.fb.group({
name: [''],
email: ['']
});


ðŸ”µ Key Difference Summary

FormGroup (Manual) FormBuilder
Uses new keyword Uses shortcut methods
More verbose Short and clean
More typing Less typing
Good for small forms Better for large forms


